algorithm_technique: Iterate through all possible numerators and denominators, use GCD to simplify and store unique fractions in a set.
problem_summary_simple: Find all unique, simplified fractions between 0 and 1 with denominators up to n.
problem_summary_technical: Generate fractions a/b where 1 <= a < b <= n, simplify using GCD, and store unique simplified forms in a set.
key_insights: The greatest common divisor (GCD) is essential for simplifying fractions.
Using a set automatically handles uniqueness of simplified fractions.
The nested loops generate all potential fractions, and GCD filtering ensures correctness.
